OL,6,FDominic Raab has said he will resign
OL,7,Ffrom government if an independent
OL,8,Finvestigation upholds allegations of
OL,9,Fbullying against him.
OL,11,FThe Justice Secretary, who is also
OL,12,FDeputy Prime Minister, asked Prime
OL,13,FMinister Rishi Sunak in November to
OL,14,Flaunch an investigation into two formal
OL,15,Fcomplaints made against him related to
OL,16,Fhis conduct towards staff.
OL,18,FIt has been alleged that Mr Raab has
OL,19,Fpreviously been "rude and aggressive"
OL,20,Ftowards staff, but he has denied these
OL,21,Fclaims.
OL,3,CDominic Raab insists he will resign if
OL,4,Cbullying allegations are upheld
